Page from our yearbook Sunday Morning: September 30, 1882, 136 years ago and BROENE... the day when future physicist Johann Wilhelm "Hance" Geiger was born in Germany.
Geiger developed a method for detecting and measuring radioactivity, an invention that eventually led to the creation of the device known as a Geiger counter.
