The inventor of World Wide Web Tim Berners-Lee begins an enterprise that aims to rival Facebook, Amazon and Google.
The latest project of technology legend, Inrupt, is a company that builds the Berners-Lee Solid open source platform.
Solid allows users to choose where to store their data and which people have permission to access certain information.
In an exclusive interview with Fast Company Berners-Lee, he joked that the intention behind Inrupt was "world domination".
"We have to do it now," he said regarding the venture.
