The application uses Solid technology that allows people to create their own “online repository of personal data” or POD.
It contains lists, to-do lists, calendar, music library and other personal and professional tools.
It looks like Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack and Spotify that are available through each browser, and at the same time all of them simultaneously.
The unique thing about the online repository of personal data is that the user determines who has access to what information.
The company calls it "the granting of authority over personal data."
The idea of Inrupt, according to the CEO of the company John Bruce, is to invest resources, processes and appropriate skills to help Solid become accessible to everyone.
